This project provides a complete analysis of NIFTY 50 stocks using Microsoft Excel. It includes historical stock data, industry-wise categorization, trend analysis, performance comparison, and summary dashboards built using formulas, charts, and data-cleaning techniques.
The goal of this project is to analyze stock performance, identify price movement patterns, calculate key metrics, and visually explain insights using Excel tools. This project is useful for beginners learning data analysis, stock analysis, and Excel-based reporting.

üìå PROJECT FEATURES
1. Data Cleaning & Preparation


Removed blanks / filled missing values


Organized stock data by rows & columns


Standardized dates, stock names, and industries


Ensured clean structure for PivotTables and lookups


2. Industry-wise Stock Classification


Used VLOOKUP / XLOOKUP to classify each stock into its correct industry


Added an industry column for deeper analysis


3. Price Trend Analysis


Identified Oldest Price and Latest Price


Calculated Percentage Change, Returns, High/Low movement


Compared performance between stocks


4. Pivot Table Summary


Created PivotTables to view:


Industry-wise average price


Best & worst performing stocks


Monthly or yearly trend summary




5. Stock Performance Dashboard


Interactive dashboard including:


Line charts


Bar charts


Sparkline mini-charts


Top gainers and losers


Industry comparison





